Here is a Julia function that meets the problem requirements:

```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    # Lowercase the column name 
    col = lowercase(col);

    # Replace any leading or trailing whitespaces with an underscore
    col = replace(col, r"^\s*" => "_");
    col = replace(col, r"\s*$" => "_");

    # Replace spaces and hyphens with an underscore
    col = replace(col, " " => "_");
    col = replace(col, "-" => "_");

    return col;
end
```
This function takes a string as input (`col`), converts it to lowercase using the `lowercase` built-in function. It then replaces any leading or trailing white spaces with an underscore by using the `replace` function with regular expressions (regex). Finally, it replaces all remaining spaces and hyphens with underscores. The cleaned column name is returned as output.
